To build on UNIX(BSD, Linux, OSX, Solaris), run the build/build script.
This sets up your system specific configure tools, builds the shared library
and compiles all test programs

To build on UNIX from distribution, run configure and then make

To build on UNIX with Eclipse, run configure and then load the project

To build on OSX with XCode 5, use the build/Blister.xcworkspace project file

To build on Windows with Visual Studio 2013, use the build/Blister.sln
project file

